, AWS deployment, and responsive UI development.\nSkills\nReact, JavaScript, TypeScript, Node.js, Express.js, MySQL, REST APIs, HTML, CSS, Tailwind CSS, AWS, Git\nExperience\nSoftware Developer | BrightApps Pvt Ltd | 2022 - Present\n- Developed and maintained internal dashboards using React and Node.js.\n- Built REST APIs for candidate and client workflows.\n- Improved query performance and optimized database access in MySQL.\nEducation\nB.Tech in Computer Science | JNTU Hyderabad | 2018 - 2022\nProjects\n- Recruitment Dashboard\n- Job Matching Portal','done',1,'2026-05-18 12:10:25','2026-05-18 12:10:31',NULL),(5,391,'uploads/resumes/resume_7_1779108086177.pdf','mohammed_ali_resume.pdf',2293,'application/pdf','\n\nMohammed Ali\nChennai, Tamil Nadu\nEmail: [Contact via Ladder Consulting] | Phone: [Contact via Ladder Consulting]\nProfessional Summary\nData analyst with 5 years of experience in reporting, dashboard creation, and business analysis using SQL, Power\nBI, Python, and Excel.\nSkills\nSQL, Python, Power BI, Excel, Dashboarding, Data Cleaning, Reporting, Data Analysis\nExperience\nSenior Data Analyst | InsightWorks | 2020 - Present\n- Built KPI dashboards for operations and sales teams.\n- Automated recurring reports using Python scripts.\n- Analyzed large datasets to identify process gaps.\nEducation\nB.Sc in Statistics | University of Madras | 2015 - 2018','done',1,'2026-05-18 12:41:26','2026-05-18 12:41:33',NULL),(6,475,'uploads/resumes/resume_8_1779169785486.pdf','rahul_verma_resume (1).pdf',2311,'application/pdf','\n\nRahul Verma\nSecunderabad, Telangana\nEmail: [Contact via Ladder Consulting] | Phone: [Contact via Ladder Consulting]\nProfessional Summary\nRecruitment and HR professional with 4 years of experience in end-to-end hiring, candidate screening, interview\ncoordination, and database management.\nSkills\nRecruitment, Talent Acquisition, Screening, Interview Coordination, ATS, Excel, Communication, Client Handling,\nOffer Management\nExperience\nHR Recruiter | TalentFirst Solutions | 2021 - Present\n- Managed sourcing for IT and non-IT roles.\n- Coordinated interviews with candidates and hiring managers.\n- Maintained recruiter pipeline and reporting dashboards.\nEducation\nMBA in HR | Osmania University | 2019 - 2021','done',1,'2026-05-19 05:49:45','2026-05-19 05:49:52',NULL),(7,515,'uploads/resumes/resume_9_1779268211612.pdf','ladder_marketing_resume_2_b2b_sales_marketer_ats.pdf',3379,'application/pdf','\n\nS. Sharma\nMarketing Executive – B2B Lead Generation\nHyderabad, Telangana | Email: [Contact via Ladder Consulting] | Phone: [Contact via Ladder Consulting] | LinkedIn:\n[Profile via Ladder Consulting]\nProfessional Summary\nMarketing professional with 2 years of experience in B2B lead generation, LinkedIn outreach, email campaigns,\nand CRM-based pipeline tracking. Experienced in working with staffing and HR service providers to generate\nqualified leads and support sales teams. Seeking to drive employer acquisition and demand generation for Ladder\nConsulting.\nCore Skills\n•\nB2B lead generation and prospecting\n•\nLinkedIn outreach and InMail campaigns\n•\nEmail marketing and follow-up sequences\n•\nCRM usage (lead status, notes, reminders)\n•\nCold calling coordination and appointment setting\n•\nCampaign performance tracking and reporting\n•\nMarket research and database building\n•\nClient communication and objection handling\nProfessional Experience\nMarketing Executive – B2B – TalentBridge HR Services, Hyderabad (Jul 2023 – Present)\n•\nGenerated and qualified leads for recruitment and staffing services through LinkedIn and email campaigns.\n•\nCollaborated with sales and recruitment teams to prioritize key accounts and schedule discovery calls.\n•\nMaintained lead data and follow-up activities in the CRM, ensuring clean and updated records.\n•\nPrepared weekly reports on outreach volumes, responses, meetings scheduled, and basic funnel metrics.\nMarketing Associate – XYZ Consulting, Hyderabad (Aug 2021 – Jun 2023)\n•\nAssisted in running email campaigns and maintaining mailing lists for consulting services.\n•\nSupported creation of basic marketing collateral such as one-pagers and case study summaries.\n•\nCoordinated with the design team to prepare presentation decks and brochures.\nEducation\n•\nMBA (Marketing), ABC Business School, Hyderabad – 2021\n•\nBCom, XYZ College, Hyderabad – 2019\nProjects\n•\nDesigned and executed a small-scale LinkedIn campaign targeting HR managers in mid-sized companies.\n•\nBuilt a prospecting list and outreach sequences for a recruitment services offering.','done',1,'2026-05-20 09:10:11','2026-06-23 07:12:04','2026-06-23 12:42:04'),(8,554,'uploads/resumes/resume_10_1779274647962.pdf','ladder_marketing_resume_3_hr_marketing_specialist_ats.pdf',3522,'application/pdf','\n\nR. Kumar\nSenior Marketing Executive – HR & Recruitment Marketing\nHyderabad, Telangana | Email: [Contact via Ladder Consulting] | Phone: [Contact via Ladder Consulting] | LinkedIn:\n[Profile via Ladder Consulting]\nProfessional Summary\nSenior marketing professional with 4+ years of experience in recruitment marketing, employer branding, and\ndigital campaigns for HR and staffing businesses. Adept at running multi-channel campaigns across LinkedIn,\nGoogle, and Meta, and aligning marketing metrics with hiring and revenue goals. Looking to lead marketing\ninitiatives for Ladder Consulting\'s HR, recruitment, and training offerings.\nCore Skills\n•\nRecruitment marketing and talent attraction campaigns\n•\nEmployer branding and content strategy\n•\nLinkedIn, Google Ads, and Meta Ads management\n•\nLead funnel optimization and nurturing\n•\nMarketing analytics and dashboard reporting\n•\nStakeholder and vendor management\n•\nTeam coordination and cross-functional collaboration\n•\nBudget tracking and ROI-focused decision making\nProfessional Experience\nSenior Marketing Executive – Recruitment Marketing – HirePlus Staffing Solutions, Hyderabad (Jan 2023 –\nPresent)\n•\nPlanned and executed recruitment marketing campaigns to attract candidates across multiple job categories.\n•\nWorked closely with HR and business heads to define target segments, messaging, and campaign timelines.\n•\nManaged LinkedIn and Meta campaigns, analyzing CPL, CTR, and conversion metrics to optimize\nperformance.\n•\nDeveloped content calendars, landing pages, and email flows for employer and candidate audiences.\nMarketing Specialist – HR Tech Startup, Hyderabad (Jul 2020 – Dec 2022)\n•\nSupported go-to-market campaigns for an HR SaaS product, focusing on SMB and mid-market clients.\n•\nCoordinated webinars, email nurture flows, and case study content with product and sales teams.\n•\nTracked campaign results in dashboards and presented insights to leadership on a monthly basis.\nEducation\n•\nMBA (Marketing & HR), DEF Institute of Management, Hyderabad – 2020\n•\nBBA, GHI College, Hyderabad – 2018\nProjects\n•\nLed an employer branding revamp project, including revamped careers page content and social storytelling.\n•\nImplemented a basic recruitment marketing framework for high-volume roles using organic and paid channels.','done',1,'2026-05-20 10:57:28','2026-05-20 10:57:28',NULL),(9,623,'uploads/resumes/resume_11_1779448273154.pdf','CV_Planning_Engineer Adnan Abdul Wase  ( Updated ).pdf',431201,'application/pdf','\n\nAdnan Abdul Wase \nMob no. [Contact via Ladder Consulting] \nMob no. [Contact via Ladder Consulting] \nEmail : [Contact via Ladder Consulting] \n \n \n \nPOST APPLIEED FOR: Planning Engineer \nOBJECTIVE: \n To obtain a challenging position and implement the acquired skills & knowledge which add \nvalue to department goals and ultimately organizational growth & objectives. I am dedicated, \ncommitted and reliable, with natural determination and achieve goals.\n \nBackground Summary: \n To be able  to  work as a planning engineer and impart my knowledge in planning operations \nlike devising methods and sequence in construction operations to ensure better performance \nin managing labor, materials and equipment’s\nEXPERIENCE: \n1. Company : Lumbini Constructions (Hyderabad ) \nProject : Elysee Residential Building High Rise ( G+15 Floors ) & Kollur Villas \nlocation  : Hyderabad Gachibowli \nDesignation : Planning Engineer \nPeriod : 4 Nov 2024 to till date \nResponsibility: \n Planning, organizing, scheduling the activities using primavera P6 and monitoring the \nprogress at site and updating the baseline program accordingly on monthly and \nweekly basis.\n Assisting senior planning engineer in preparation of bar charts, delay reports etc.\n Timely alarming PM regarding the delays occurring at site from our side and from \nsubcontractor side and its effects on our completion date of the projects.\n Submitting daily, weekly and monthly reports to client/consultant.\n Visiting the site and taking the updates and progress photographs and submitting \nthem to client in a proper way.\n Supervising the programs received from subcontractors and notifying them the delays \nas and when required.\n\n Preparing cash flow chart and the resource curve.\n Identifying the late nomination of provisional sum sub-contractors and its effects on \nour program.\n2. Company : Precon Constructions (Hyderabad) \nProject : High Rise Building (G+12 Floors) \nDesignation   : Project Planner \nPeriod : 1\nst\n Jan 2023 to 30 \nth\n Oct 2024 \nResponsibility: \n Planning, Scheduling, Monitoring, Coordination of all planning activities of Construction.\n Estimation of all required resources (Equipment, Manpower and Material) as per scope \nof work.\n Reporting (S-curves, Critical activities and delayed activities) and examining the effect of \nprogress  against  the  baseline  schedule.  Generation  of  look  ahead  plan  and  ensure \neffective and accurate reporting as per applicable standards.\n Coordinating with engineering, procurement & construction teams for smooth & timely \ncompletion of project.\n Loading/ updating the Actual in Primavera to monitor progress.\n Analyzing & highlighting the factors which are causing delays in progress.\n \n3. Company : BCES Constructions \nProject : High Rise Building (G+10 Floors) \nDesignation   : Planning Engineer \nPeriod : 3\nrd\n Apr 2021 to 29\nth\n Dec 2022 \nResponsibility: \n Planning, Scheduling, Monitoring, Coordination of all planning activities of Construction.\n Estimation of all required resources (Equipment, Manpower and Material) as per scope \nof work.\n Reporting (S-curves, Critical activities and delayed activities) and examining the effect of \nprogress  against  the  baseline  schedule.  Generation  of  look  ahead  plan  and  ensure \neffective and accurate reporting as per applicable standards.\n Coordinating with engineering, procurement & construction teams for smooth & timely \ncompletion of project.\n\n Preparation of Project Daily/weekly & monthly progress reports for client submission.\n Attending weekly meetings with Project Manager and Team to discuss and resolve the issues.\n Preparation of Recovery Plans to measure the Project progress accurately.\n Preparation of Revise Schedules after the approval of E.O.T.\n \nEDUCATIONAL QUALIFICATION \n Matriculation – 2015 (Gowtham Model School) -77%\n Diploma – Civil 2018 ( Quli Qutub Shah Polytechnic ) -90%\n Bachelors - Civil 2021 (Mahaveer Institute of Science & Technology ) -80%\nSOFTWARE/ COURSES \n Project Planning & Co-ordination using Primavera: P6. /8.2/22.12/24.12. \n Design Tools : AutoCAD. Latest version \n Packages : MS-Office (Word, Excel and other applications) \nSKILLS \n \n Proficiency in computer-based planning tools, e.g. Primavera P6. \n Self-motivated & ability to learn new concepts quickly for the consistent success of the \norganization. \n Knowledge of construction sequence \n Reading & Interpretation of drawings and specification (accurate take off from drawings). \n Stron