c KYC reviews and remediation of incomplete or outdated customer information \n Maintained accurate records and audit trails for regulatory and compliance purposes. \n Coordinated with internal teams to improve turnaround time and maintain operational efficiency in KYC processing. \n Demonstrated strong attention to detail in handling large volumes of documentation with minimal errors. \n \nFINANCE PROJECT \nFinancial Performance Analysis – Karnataka Cotton Industry, Afzalpur \n3-Month Internship Project \n Analyzed financial statements to assess profitability, operational efficiency, and business performance trends.  \n Prepared structured financial analysis reports that improved visibility into revenue and expense patterns.  \n Evaluated accounting data and transaction records to identify discrepancies and improve reporting accuracy.  \n Leveraged Advanced Excel functions including Pivot Tables, Charts, and VLOOKUP to streamline financial data analysis.  \n Supported finance operations through accurate documentation, ledger review, and reconciliation activities.  \n Strengthened understanding of balance sheets, cash flow statements, ratio analysis, and financial controls.  \n \nSKILLS \n Financial Reporting & Analysis  \n Accounting Bookkeeping  \n Ledger Reconciliation \n Journal Entries & Documentation  \n Financial Statement Analysis  \n Advanced Excel and MS PowerPoint \n Tally Prime  \n \n GST Fundamentals  \n MS Office  \n Data Accuracy & Compliance  \n Team Collaboration  \n Adaptability \n Communication   \n \nLANGUAGES \n English  \n Kannada \n Hindi \n \nDECLARATION \nI hereby declare that the above information is true to the best of my knowledge.  \nPlace : Hyderabad                                                                                Gouri Shivanand Neelur \n \n ','done',0,'2026-06-15 11:12:57','2026-06-15 11:12:57',NULL),(30,710,'uploads/resumes/resume_3_1781521977216_bxpggl.pdf','Nithish reddy resume F (1).pdf',94496,'application/pdf','\n\nP.NITHISH KUMAR REDDY\nJr.Electrical Engineer\n[Contact via Ladder Consulting] Hyderabad, Telangana\n[Contact via Ladder Consulting]\nABOUT ME\nEnthusiastic Junior Electrical Engineer with 2 years of experience in solar power plant coordination, electrical\nsystems and techno-commercial activities. Skilled in renewable energy technologies, grid connection, power\ndistribution, and providing tender technical support. Passionate about advancing clean energy solutions, with\na goal to specialize in solar, hydro, wind, and energy storage systems.\nEDUCATION\nBACHELOR OF TECHNOLOGY (B.TECH) IN ELECTRICAL AND ELECTRONICS ENGINEERING\nINTERMEDIATE (MPC)\nGeethanjali College of Engineering and Technology\nNarayana Junior College\n2020 – 2024\n2018 – 2020\nSKILL\nGoogle Earth Pro\nMapping \nPvSyst\nAutoCAD \nTechno Commercial\nSite Execution  \nMS Office & Excel\nWORK EXPERIENCE\nSirmour Small Hydro  Power  Pvt. Ltd. – Junior Electrical EngineerJUNE 2024 – PRESENT\nAs a Junior Electrical Engineer, I have been actively involved in the execution and coordination of a 15 MW solar\npower plant project. My role includes conducting site coordination, performing design evaluation, assisting in\ntechno-commercial activities such as intermediate-level budget preparation and technical comparison, and\nproviding tender technical support. I also use tools such as Google Earth Pro to evaluate tender documents\nand identify suitable substations for project locations.\nAssisted in techno-commercial tasks, including intermediate-level budget preparation\nand technical comparison of project requirements.\nCoordinated site activities for a 15 MW solar power plant, including grid connection.\nI had successfully completed my internship at South Central Railway, Carriage Workshop, Lallaguda on\n“Working of 25KW Alternator and RRU”.\n I had successfully completed my internship with Cantilever labs on“Artificial Intelligence & Machine\nLearning” . \nChanakya High School\nSCHOOLING – SSC\n2017 – 2018\nProvided tender technical support for renewable energy projects.\nUtilized Google Earth Pro for analyzing tender documents and identifying the best substations\nfor project integration.\nPrepared project documentation, drawings, and reports using AutoCAD and MS Office tools\nINTERNSHIP EXPERIENCE\nAwarded with “Certificate of Appreciation” for coordinated Bhaswara 2023 held at Geethanjali college.\nACHIEVEMENTS\nAwarded with a certificate for completion of project “FAKE NEWS DETECTION” using AIM\nAwarded “Consistent Contributor” Certificate of Recognition by Sangamam Power Projects Pvt. Ltd.\nTender technical support \n[Profile via Ladder Consulting] via Ladder Consulting]\npullaiahgari-1b4066227','done',0,'2026-06-15 11:12:57','2026-06-15 11:12:57',NULL),(31,711,'uploads/resumes/resume_3_1781521977217_vzmsp9.pdf','PREM ACCOUNTANT SPEEDEX.pdf',245486,'application/pdf','\n\n \n                                                   CURRICULUM VITAE \nPersonal Information \nName: Prem Pratik Upadhyay \nMobile: [Contact via Ladder Consulting] \nEmail: [Contact via Ladder Consulting] \nAddress: Lakshmi Narayan Bagh Goshamahal Nampally Hyderabad Telangana. \n \nCareer Objective \nA dedicated and enthusiastic Bachelor of Commerce graduate seeking an entry-level position in \naccounting, finance, or business operations. Eager to contribute to organizational success through \na strong work ethic, academic knowledge, and willingness to learn. \n \nEducational Qualification \nQualification Institution Board/University Year Percentage/CGPA \nB.Com \nSt. Francis Xavier’s \nDegree College \nOsmania University  2019  [70%] \nC.E.C (12th) New St Francis junior] Board of Intermediate  2015 [60%] \nSSC (10th) Slate the School  \nSecondary certificate \nSchool  \n2012 [60 %] \n \nTechnical Skills \n• MS Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint) \n• Tally ERP 9 / Tally Prime (if applicable) \n• Basic knowledge of Accounting Principles \n• Internet and Email proficiency 